At __Calais__ we ended up in a dreadful campsite — almost like a gypsy encampment. The loos, I was told, were covered in crap + so were the urinals. An Australian motorcyclist + his girlfriend were nervous about having their belongings stolen during the night (a nervous Australian?) + we offered to have them in our van for safekeeping. So Simon made them a cup of tea + we had their clobber on the floor.
    As soon as we woke up on Friday 10th August, Simon returned their belongings + we drove off to a carpark to have breakfast. We went to a supermarket + boarded the ferry.
    Once we were back in England we went to west of Folkestone to see the Channel Tunnel Exhibition Centre;
